# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib
bin/*


# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env
build/.env

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# Stray binaries built at the repo root.
# The canonical build output is `bin/gibson` (already covered by `bin/*` above) —
# produced by `make bin`. Running plain `go build` at the repo root drops a
# `./gibson` here; this anchored entry stops it from ever being committed.
# Do NOT replace with the bare path `gibson` — that would shadow any future file
# named gibson in any subdirectory.
/gibson

# E2E helper / lint binaries built ad-hoc into the module root
/route-drift
/fixtures-lint

# E2E fixture binaries built ad-hoc by `go build` next to their main.go
tests/e2e/fixtures/agents/probe/probe
tests/e2e/fixtures/targets/test-target/test-target

# Claude Code internal scheduler state
.claude/

# Build artifacts and codegen scratch (added 2026-05-10 cleanup)
/.tmp/
/audit-csv-gen
/tenant-owner-backfill
